devotion /dɪˈvəʊʃən/

1. N-UNCOUNT Devotion is great love, affection, or admiration for someone. 热爱 

例： At first she was flattered by his devotion. 最初他的挚爱使她感到受宠若惊。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Devotion is commitment to a particular activity. 献身 

例： ...devotion to the cause of the people and to socialism. …对于人民的事业和社会主义的献身。

